definition.value: A member of the class of  dibenzofurans that is  dibenzofuran substituted by methoxy groups at positions 3, 4 and 7 and hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 8.
A monocarboxylic acid amide in which 2,6-dimethylphenylaniline and isobutyric acid have combined to form the amide bond; used as a local anaesthetic.

An N-sulfonylurea that is 1-tosylurea in which a hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 3 is replaced by an azepan-1-yl group. A hypoglycemic agent, it is used for the treatment of type 2 diabetes mellitus.
